# KaJota mobile — Breet Builder Grant (Jun 15, 2026 deadline) env template.
#
# Copy to `.env.breet` (gitignored) before running the Breet integration
# flow. Pairs with docs/HACKS.md → "Breet Builder Grant" for the full
# walkthrough + Loom recording script.
#
# Breet's API surface is small: per-user crypto wallet addresses,
# webhook for inbound payments, settlement to NGN/USDC/USDT/GHS. Fits
# the existing FundWallet + OrderPayment + (potentially) Withdraw
# screens with minimal new surface.

# ---- Breet API credentials ----------------------------------------

# API key from the Breet developer dashboard (https://breet.io/developers).
# Server-side use only — never bundle in the mobile app. The mobile
# app calls KaJota's backend, which proxies to Breet with this key.
BREET_API_KEY=

# Webhook signing secret — Breet posts a signed payload to your
# backend when a deposit is detected. Verify the signature before
# crediting the user.
BREET_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# API base. Use the sandbox while iterating, prod for the Loom
# recording.
# BREET_API_BASE=https://api.sandbox.breet.io
BREET_API_BASE=https://api.breet.io

# ---- Settlement currency ------------------------------------------

# What Breet auto-converts inbound crypto to. Options: NGN / USDC /
# USDT / GHS. Match the credited wallet currency on KaJota's side.
BREET_SETTLEMENT_CURRENCY=NGN

# ---- Integration target -------------------------------------------

# Which KaJota flow this build is wiring. Pick the one shipping
# fastest for the Loom demo:
#
#   wallet-deposit  - FundWallet screen gains a "Pay with crypto"
#                     option. Easiest fit; Breet generates per-user
#                     address, webhook credits the wallet.
#   order-payment   - PaymentOptionModal at checkout gains a
#                     stablecoin tile. Per-order address, webhook
#                     marks order paid.
#   withdraw        - WithdrawAmount gains an off-ramp option.
#                     Requires Breet's send-out API surface (less
#                     certain; verify with their docs).
BREET_INTEGRATION_TARGET=wallet-deposit

# ---- Webhook receiver ---------------------------------------------

# Public URL where Breet's webhook lands. Local dev: tunnel via
# ngrok / cloudflare; production: kajota-mobile-backend `hackathon/breet`
# branch exposing /webhooks/breet.
BREET_WEBHOOK_URL=

# ---- Compliance ---------------------------------------------------

# Breet requires KYC/KYB. KaJota already collects KYC via the
# existing onboarding flow; map the existing fields to Breet's
# customer-create endpoint. Document the field mapping in HACKS.md.

